<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib">437. Letouzey, Victor. Colour and Colour Measurement in the Graphic Industries. Translated by V.G.W. Harrison. London: Pitman, 1957. 62 pp. Bibl., B/W illus., color illus. </p><p class="annot">Translated from the French, this is a concise presentation of color for printing from a technical viewpoint. Sections cover color measurement in the graphic arts, mutual influences of adjacent colors, and mechanics of absorption. The 53 illustrations, many in color, present the information in a straightforward and graphic manner and make the basic principles of color printing intelligible to students of art and design.</p></div>
